sections.title: 📘 Course Outline: Introduction to Agent Completion V2 Toolset

contents.body: ## 📘 Course Outline: *Introduction to Agent Completion V2 Toolset* ### **Overview** **Objective**: Understand the role of tool-use in Agent Completion V2 tasks. * Agent Completion involves agents using tools to complete user tasks across geolocation, calendar, system settings, and more. * Tools operate via API-like parameters: agents must provide required inputs and interpret structured outputs. * Correct tool-use improves user satisfaction and task completion accuracy.\ \ [**See Tool Set Document Here**](https://app.outlier.ai/en/expert/instruction/683e729ecaf6d16374e6fc5b)

A fundamental part of this project are the tools that the model will use to fulfill your requests throughout the conversation, such as creating an event, telling you how to get to a place, giving you the link to a Spotify playlist or telling you what the weather is like in a certain place, among others. There are more than 100 tools that the model will be able to use. You can see all the tools and related information in [this document](https://app.outlier.ai/en/expert/instruction/683e729ecaf6d16374e6fc5b). Here, in addition to all the tools available, you will see which parameters are essential for the tools to work and which are not. This will allow you to know what steps the model will have to take before using a certain tool and thanks to this knowledge you will be able to know what to criticize and correct. At the beginning of each task, you will see which subset of tools are available for each model. You will also need to acknowledge your understanding of this by properly selecting which tools are available from the checkbox options.

### **Baseline Tools** The “Time, Device & System Control” Tool Domain is foundational and will be included in the subset of tools for every task: * get_system_settings * set_system_settings * get_current_location * get_current_iso_8601_datetime_with_utc_offset

### **Tool Subsets** The model will only have access to a specific set of tools for each task. See the “**Tool Subsets”** section of the [Tool Set document](https://app.outlier.ai/en/expert/instruction/683e729ecaf6d16374e6fc5b) for information on which tools are available for each of the domains provided at the beginning of each task.

### **🧭 Module 1: Geolocation & Place Tools**

These tools help agents work with real-world locations, providing functionality such as place search, reverse geocoding, and travel directions.

#### 🔍 `search_place`

**Purpose**: Find places based on a name, address, or category.\
**Example**: “coffee near Boston”\
**Key Inputs**: `query` (required), optional: `country`, `language`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `radius`\
**Returns**: A list of matching places, each with a `place_id`, coordinates, and formatted address.

---

#### 🏢 `place_details`

**Purpose**: Retrieve rich information about a place using its `place_id`.\
**Key Inputs**: `place_id` (required)\
**Returns**: Phone number, operating hours, address, user reviews, etc.

---

#### 🗺️ `get_directions`

**Purpose**: Generate travel directions between two known places.\
**Key Inputs**:

* Required: `origin` and `destination` (as `place_id`s)
* Optional: `departure_time` or `arrival_time`, `mode` (e.g., walking), `traffic_model`\
  **Returns**: Travel time, step-by-step directions.

---

#### 🔁 `convert_place_id_lat_lon_address`

**Purpose**: Convert between `place_id`, geographic coordinates, and human-readable address.\
**Key Inputs**: At least one of: `place_id`, `latitude + longitude`, or `formatted_address`\
**Returns**: The other two forms.

### 📅 **Module 2: Calendar Management Tools**

These tools allow agents to create and manage calendars for organizing events.

#### 🗂️ `create_calendar`

**Purpose**: Create a new calendar.\
**Key Inputs**: `title` (required)\
**Returns**: A unique `calendar_id`.

---

#### 🔍 `search_calendars`

**Purpose**: Find calendars by title (semantic search) or exact ID.\
**Key Inputs**: `title` or `calendar_id`\
**Returns**: List of matching calendars.

---

#### ✏️ `modify_calendar`

**Purpose**: Rename an existing calendar.\
**Key Inputs**: `calendar_id`, new `title`\
**Returns**: Confirmation of change.

---

#### ❌ `remove_calendar`

**Purpose**: Permanently delete a calendar and its events.\
**Key Inputs**: `calendar_id` (required)

---

### 📆 **Module 3: Calendar Event Tools**

These tools enable agents to create, search, update, or delete events in calendars.

#### ➕ `create_calendar_event`

**Purpose**: Add a new event to a calendar.\
**Key Inputs**:

* Required: `calendar_id`, `title`, `start_datetime`, `end_datetime`
* Optional: attendees, recurrence, address or coordinates, etc.\
  **Supports**: Recurrence patterns, location, all-day events, multiple attendees.

---

#### 🔎 `search_calendar_events`

**Purpose**: Find events using rich filters.\
**Key Inputs**: Search by time range, title, attendee, recurrence, or location\
**Returns**: Matching event instances with full context.

---

#### 📝 `modify_calendar_event`

**Purpose**: Change an existing event.\
**Key Inputs**: `calendar_event_id` (required), any fields to update (title, time, location, etc.)\
**Supports**: Updating recurring event series or single instances.

---

#### 🗑️ `remove_calendar_event`

**Purpose**: Delete an event by ID.\
**Key Inputs**: `calendar_event_id`\
**Note**: Deleting a recurring event requires using the parent event ID.

### 📆 **Module 3: Calendar Event Tools**

These tools enable agents to create, search, update, or delete events in calendars.

#### ➕ `create_calendar_event`

**Purpose**: Add a new event to a calendar.\
**Key Inputs**:

* Required: `calendar_id`, `title`, `start_datetime`, `end_datetime`
* Optional: attendees, recurrence, address or coordinates, etc.\
  **Supports**: Recurrence patterns, location, all-day events, multiple attendees.

---

#### 🔎 `search_calendar_events`

**Purpose**: Find events using rich filters.\
**Key Inputs**: Search by time range, title, attendee, recurrence, or location\
**Returns**: Matching event instances with full context.

---

#### 📝 `modify_calendar_event`

**Purpose**: Change an existing event.\
**Key Inputs**: `calendar_event_id` (required), any fields to update (title, time, location, etc.)\
**Supports**: Updating recurring event series or single instances.

---

#### 🗑️ `remove_calendar_event`

**Purpose**: Delete an event by ID.\
**Key Inputs**: `calendar_event_id`\
**Note**: Deleting a recurring event requires using the parent event ID.

### ⚙️ **Module 4: System Tools**

These tools control or query the agent’s device/system state.

#### 📡 `get_system_settings`

**Purpose**: Retrieve the current state of system features.\
**Returns**: Wi-Fi, location services, low battery mode, and timezone info.

---

#### 🔧 `set_system_settings`

**Purpose**: Modify system settings.\
**Key Inputs**: Any of: `wifi`, `location_service`, `cellular`, `low_battery_mode`, `locale`, `utc_offset_seconds`\
**Use Case**: Enabling Wi-Fi or turning on location services before using tools that depend on them.

---

#### 📍 `get_current_location`

**Purpose**: Get the device’s current latitude, longitude, and address.\
**Returns**: Location coordinates and formatted address.\
**Note**: Location services must be enabled first.

contents.question: **Q1.** The model will have access to all tools listed in the tool set document for every task.
**Q2.** What tool would you use to retrieve user reviews for a restaurant?
**Q3.** You want to create a bi-weekly recurring event. Which parameters could be needed?
**Q4.** Which tool is used to rename an existing calendar?
**Q5.** Which of the following requires a `place_id` as input?
**Q6.** What is the minimum required field to use `search_place`?
**Q7.** `get_current_location` can be used without enabling location services.
**Q8.** `create_calendar_event` always requires a location to be set.
**Q9.** `set_system_settings` can be used to change your locale and timezone.
**Q9.** `get_market_tickers` can be used to search for prices and information about a single individual ticker.
**Q10.** The `product_search` tool searches across several different online retail platforms, yielding results across a wide variety of stores.
**Q11.** The `weather_forecast` tool takes in a formatted address as a parameter (e.g. 100 Street, Whoville, US).
